<meta name="description" content="Protein sequences are submitted to auto cross covariance (ACC) transformation into uniform equal-length vectors. ACC is a protein sequence mining method, which has been applied to quantitative structure-activity relationships (QSAR) studies of peptides with different length. 
The principal properties of the amino acids are represented by E descriptors.They describe amino acid hydrophobicity, molecular size, helix-forming propensity, relative abundance of amino acids and  Î²-strand forming propensity. 
The proteins are classified by k-nearest neighbor algorithm (KNN). 
">
